      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the dreaded stagnant sourdough starter! It sounds like your little critter is feeling a bit under the weather. But fear not, there are a few things we can try to help it perk up.\n\nFirst, let's talk about stirring. Give your starter a good stir with a wooden spoon or a dough hook attachment on your stand mixer. This will help distribute the flour and yeast evenly throughout the mixture, giving it a little boost.\n\nNext, let's consider the jar. Make sure it's the right size for your starter. A jar that's too small can make it difficult for the starter to grow and can lead to stagnation. If you're using a glass jar, try switching to a plastic one, as they can be easier for the starter to breathe.\n\nFinally, let's talk about the feeding. Try feeding your starter with a 1:1:1 ratio of flour, water, and starter. This should give it a balanced diet and help it regain its vitality.\n\nRemember, every sourdough starter is unique, and sometimes it just takes a little extra care and attention to get it back on track. Keep an eye on it, and don't hesitate to reach out if you need more guidance!",
